					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10043907#post-4130944</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10043907/scp-4729#post-4130944</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 25 Jan 2019 23:56:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Voct</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>392303</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It bothers me to use the term &quot;fractal&quot; when discussing something from 1972. Mandelbrot only coined the word in 1975. Foundation researchers wouldn't have called them &quot;fractal ice structures&quot;, and it feels wrong to assume that they'd go back to an old report, look for the place where the ice structures were described in complex mathematical terminology, and update it to account for new vocabulary.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10043907#post-4129515</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10043907/scp-4729#post-4129515</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 24 Jan 2019 17:10:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Really enjoyed this. As others have said, the restraint shown here in the description makes it a lot better. Less is more and all. There's a lot to be read into this between the lines. My only suggestion for improvement would be perhaps giving a bit more detail on the mask in the containment procedures(maybe they stored it or are studying it) and the early description. It's a good ending for the mask to be removed before it perished, but it might hit harder if we could imagine it as more than silicon polymers in the shape of a breathing mask. Other than that I don't have any complaints for this one. Really good picture choice as well. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
